            "answer_text": "When I was around 13 years old, I spent the night at my friends house and stayed up all night playing video games. When I got home it was Saturday; the day I always do my chores. When I got home I felt pretty tired so I asked my mom if I could sleep for just a few hours. She said yes but I better get up to do my chores. I went in bed and instantly fell asleep. When I woke up, it looked like it was morning so I checked the time and it was around 9:30. I thought it was Sunday so I got ready for church but no one was up. I woke up my parents and urgently told them that we needed to hurry and get to church. My mom told me it was Monday! I was amazed that I had slept for more than 24 hours. So my conclusion is that humans can sleep longer if you\u2019re mentally tired than if you\u2019re physically tired. ",
