            "answer_text": "If they are both mentally and physically tired\u2026. A lot! I just went back to Europe from Australia and I hadn't sleep for around 2 days, took intercontinental flights and stood awake on the plane. So far I have slept 22 hrs in interrupted. I only woke up to go to the bathroom. If I had something to allow me to stay in bed without the need to go to the bathroom I think I could sleep up to 30-35 hours. I woke up one hour ago, eating now and all I can think is to go back to bed to sleep. The weird thing is that I don't feel the fatigue on my body that much. The sleepiness is 90% mental. Like my brain needs sleep more than my body. ",
